      "tAsideSectionIntroductionLabel00": "Introduction",
      "tAsideSectionIntroductionDescription00": "During my time at Sun West Mortgage Company, I had the opportunity to contribute towards their flagship product. AngelAi, affectionately called Angel, was a mortgage focused alternative to ChatGPT that provided 100% warranteed answers to all your financial questions. It was marketed as a personal assistant, dedicated to simplifying and enhancing your financial transactions. With a special focus on mortgage-related activities, AngelAI is here to revolutionize the way you manage your finances. Prepare to embark on a journey where financial tasks become a breeze, with the unwavering support of your trusted companion.",
      "tAsideSectionProblemLabel00": "Problem",
      "tAsideSectionProblemDescription00": "Despite successful marketing efforts the site's daily active user count was not scaling proportionately with the site's new user metrics. At the time we had not identified why this was despite knowing that it was the right product at the right time for the right market.",
      "tAsideSectionActionLabel00": "Action",
      "tAsideSectionActionDescription00": "Initial research provided several reasons why there would be a large discrepancy between new users and users creating accounts. We we able to rule out many of the common reasons right away as the barrier to entry couldn't be lower and at the time AI chats were the new hotness. The service being backed by a bank helped provide credibility and the bank's long standing history secured the user's trust. While every system could be improved in every way, the primary concern that stood out was the possibility of a poor user experience. Our Quality Control department was testing everything before it was released while our Chief Design Officer and Chief Executive Officer were approving everything to ensure that it fit within the brand guidelines. Looking into the chat logs I identified several chats where the users seemed to abruptly stop the conversation despite being engaged previously. While some amount of this is to be expected on a product marketed largely for mobile devices I felt that the rates were abnormally high. With this data in mind, I designed a full stack approach to start tracking user errors encountered on the client. This included a figma prototype showing how errors could be caught gracefully, a new Mongoose Schema, node endpoint and how everything would work together. The goal was to provide timely notifications to the development team whenever an error occured, where the error occured, who it happened to, and an error stack so that the error could be traced and properly addressed. After getting approval from management, this solution was developed, tested, implemented, and released to production. In the first couple weeks after release we were shocked to see just how many errors were being sent in from the new system. I was able to help junior developers understand the errors, identify the root cause, and determine an efficient approach to resolve the issue without creating additional bugs. With the issues identified and more complete picture of what our users were experiencing, management made the decision to migrate the code base over to TypeScript. Despite being new to TypeScript at the time, I was one of three developers chosen for the migration task and we were able to produce outstanding results.",
