      "tAsideSectionActionDescription01": "As the figma design was already set in stone, my role with this project was more straightforward. Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams, we developed a detailed roadmap and prioritized features to ensure timely delivery of the MVP. Leveraging agile methodologies, we swiftly moved from planning to development. With my specialization in CSS, I converted the figma wireframe into a more accurate depiction of the CSS box model and advised Allan Tham on various approaches to bypass obstacles. I also worked with Allireza on the backend Java and SQL systems to ensure that authentication, authorization, and signature details were kept private. We efficiently released the MVP a week ahead of schedule. This allowed for invite-only testing where we utilized agile methodologies to quickly iterate and respond to user feedback. During a sprint retrospective, I was able to predict potential issues with accessibility and present different ways we could solve the upcoming issue.",
      "tAsideSectionResultLabel01": "Result",
      "tAsideSectionResultDescription01": "AiSign proved to be a game-changer for our company, as we successfully replaced third-party solutions like DocuSign company-wide. This not only allowed us to cancel a $500k contract but also showcased our team's ability to deliver innovative solutions under tight deadlines. AiSign's success underscored our commitment to excellence and solidified our position as leaders in the financial technology sector.",
