      "tAsideSectionIntroductionLabel12": "Introduction",
      "tAsideSectionIntroductionDescription12": "MoreRetain was conceived as a groundbreaking solution to the perennial challenges encountered in language learning. It aimed to tackle mispronunciation and skill retention head-on, providing an immersive language learning experience unlike any other. By leveraging cutting-edge automated speech technologies, MoreRetain promised to reshape the landscape of language education.",
      "tAsideSectionProblemLabel12": "Problem",
      "tAsideSectionProblemDescription12": "Traditional language learning methods often struggle to address the nuanced difficulties of pronunciation and long-term skill retention. MoreRetain set out to bridge this gap, aiming to provide users with real-time feedback on their pronunciation and personalized learning experiences to enhance skill retention.",
      "tAsideSectionActionLabel12": "Action",
      "tAsideSectionActionDescription12": "Development began quickly on the initial solution, called polyglot. It was a barebones UI formated like Google Translate that also offered some extra functionality to encourage users to interact with the software. After the core functionality was realized, the initial release was slow to be adopted due to the standard UI. Because of this, I reached out to Of_space who provided their langauge learning site design. The core of the behance project was left untouched while the text was updated to work with different langauges and released their implementation for pronunciation feedback right, implementing cutting-edge features to deliver real-time speech-to-text feedback and customizable dictionaries. By harnessing the power of Angular and integrating Google Translate's API, we laid a robust foundation for future enhancements and scalability.",
      "tAsideSectionResultsLabel12": "Results",
      "tAsideSectionResultsDescription12": "While Roseta became incredibly popular in the news for their implementation of pronunciation feedback, MoreRetain was developing this feature in parallel before it's announcmeent. The introduction of automated pronunciation feedback garnered widespread acclaim, marking a significant step forward in language learning technology. Users appreciated the personalized learning experience and real-time feedback, setting the stage for further innovations in the field. I take pride in knowing that I was able to identify a need in an industry and develop a software solution to solve the problem. These days, my design skills have improved dramatically, and I'd love to touch this project up, especially after signing in, but with major personal projects like Callouts Evolved already doing so well it's hard to dedicate the time. For now, it stands to show how much I've learned and how far I've come."
